Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Web Developer* position with *San Francisco Bay University (SFBU)*. I bring over three years of professional experience building responsive web interfaces, front-end platforms, and data-driven UI systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade front-end interfaces and interactive web experiences that directly reflect the *UI/UX depth and responsive web development sensibility* this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed a React Flow and TypeScript visual workflow platform with *responsive*, *mobile-first* layouts and an intuitive drag-and-drop UI — prioritizing cross-device user experience and visual consistency across the full interface. Alongside it, I developed real-time progress dashboards using React and Redis, surfacing live execution status through clean, accessible HTML/CSS components aligned to product design specifications. To ensure these web interfaces remained reliable, I built GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines for front-end deployments, running automated test suites that enforced UI consistency and caught visual regressions before each production release. I also built an interactive React front-end for a documentation search tool, delivering a searchable, filterable web interface that connects users to product information and ready-to-run REST API examples with minimal friction. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed interactive React data visualizations for business stakeholders — translating complex PostgreSQL query results into intuitive, responsive web dashboards with clean UI/UX presentation — and maintained cloud-backed file services across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO, giving me direct experience with the cross-department communication and technical precision required to keep high-traffic digital properties accurate, performant, and aligned with organizational standards. Together, these roles have prepared me to *contribute meaningfully to maintaining and enhancing SFBU's digital presence* across web properties, and to deliver web experiences that place students at the center of every design decision.

My academic and independent project work has given me a rigorous foundation in TypeScript, systems architecture, and engineering discipline that reinforces my front-end development capabilities. Through building Dark Factory — a distributed TypeScript and Elixir orchestrator that executes agent tasks across multi-machine systems with retries and timeout handling — I developed the habit of designing for reliability and delivering polished digital output under real-world constraints. This systems-level rigor, combined with my front-end experience at Sperse and Qualitest, prepares me to work effectively across SFBU's IT team and department stakeholders — *translating design concepts into engaging, accessible web interfaces* and ensuring the university's online presence reflects both its brand standards and its commitment to every student it serves.

I have always been passionate about *inclusive, innovative education and lifelong student success* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *SFBU's mission to set the national standard for engaged, transformative higher education in service of the common good*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

